The paper deals with the problem of zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (CV). The proposed approach involves the use of neural networks and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the use of attributes and similarity measures, which are relevant to natural language processing (CL) and multimedia (MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. cs.CL and cs.MM are less likely but still possible due to the use of attributes and similarity measures.
